      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "> Also - do you think we need a segwitV0 function like this as well? As far as I can grep there's only 2 such signing operations in `p2p_segwit.py` so maybe that's more work than its worth.\r\n\r\nGood point -- I think it would be nice to introduce similar functions for other signature types (e.g. `sign_input_segwitv0`) for consistency reasons. Might be worth a follow-up, together with some other improvements pointed out in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28025#discussion_r1253580835 (type annotations, input range checks etc.)? If anyone wants to tackle that, feel free to ping me as reviewer.",
